The paper deals with named entity recognition (NER) in social media, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related areas. The paper also proposes a neural network architecture, which involves training and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of contextualized representation models and character-level embeddings suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category. The paper also deals with pre-processing errors, which can be seen as a form of noise reduction, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval in social media, which can be seen as a form of search, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category.
